Method Detail

annotateInput

public String annotateInput(String inputData,
                            String modelFile)
Annotates the inputData based on the modelFile and returns the the pairs of arguments where a given relation holds.

Parameters:
inputData - a test set
modelFile - an absolute path to a model
Returns:
pairs of arguments

Note that the inputData has to be prsented as follows:

  • each word takes one line
  • sentences are separated by newlines
  • annotations of the named entities are done in the IOB format (a word and its tag are separated by a space)

Example:

PROTEIN1 B-protein

regulates O

PROTEIN2 B-protein

. O

PROTEIN1a B-protein

PROTEIN1b I-protein

binds O

to O

PROTEIN2 B-protein

. O
